[35m[coding-review][0m         (2/20) step 3/3 | **NEW-01** | **REJECT** | `src/index.ts:47` | **Non-null assertion operator (`!`) used on state property.** In `evolve` for `StockShipped`, `newState.reservations[event.reservationId]!` is used. While `decide` checks for reservation existence, `evolve` must be robust as it is used for replaying all events. If an event stream is corrupted or an event is applied out of order, this will throw a runtime error. | Remove `!` and handle the case where the reservation might be missing (e.g., ignore the event or use a default of 0), ensuring the function never throws as per README requirements. |
